import numpy as np

In [4]:
dataset_url = "/content/dataset/"

train_url = dataset_url + "training_set/"
test_url = dataset_url + "test_set/test_set/"

train_dogs_url = train_url + "dogs/"
train_cats_url = train_url + "cats/"
test_dogs_url = test_url + "dogs/"
test_cats_url = test_url + "cats/"

img_size = (64, 64)
# img_size = (128, 128)
batch_size = 256
In [5]:
X_train = []
y_train = []

with tf.device("/GPU:0"):
    for train_dog_url in tqdm(os.listdir(train_dogs_url)):
        if "dog" not in train_dog_url: continue
        img = np.array(tf.keras.preprocessing.image.load_img(
            train_dogs_url + train_dog_url,
            target_size = img_size,
        ))
        X_train.append(img)
        y_train.append(1)

    for train_cat_url in tqdm(os.listdir(train_cats_url)):
        if "cat" not in train_cat_url: continue
        img = np.array(tf.keras.preprocessing.image.load_img(
            train_cats_url + train_cat_url,
            target_size = img_size,
        ))
        X_train.append(img)
        y_train.append(0)

In [8]:
with tf.device("/GPU:0"):
    for folder in os.listdir("fetched_dataset/"):
        for anim in ['cat', 'dog']:
            sub_folder = f"fetched_dataset/{folder}/{anim}s/"
            for img in tqdm(os.listdir(sub_folder)):
                img_url = sub_folder + img

                img = np.array(tf.keras.preprocessing.image.load_img(
                    img_url,
                    target_size = img_size,
                ))

                X_train.append(img)
                y_train.append(["cat", "dog"].index(anim))

# MUTATING THE DATA

img_data_gen = tf.keras.preprocessing.image.ImageDataGenerator()
def tranform_image(img):
    return img_data_gen.apply_transform(img, {
        'theta': np.random.uniform(0, 360),
        'flip_horizontal': np.random.randint(0, 2),
        'flip_vertical': np.random.randint(0, 2),
    })

n_mutated_data = 800

for i in np.random.randint(0, len(X_train), size=(n_mutated_data)):
    X_train[i] = tranform_image(X_train[i])

Modelling¶

In [16]:
from tensorflow.keras import models, layers

model = models.Sequential([
    # Setting Input Shape
    layers.Input(shape = img_size + (3,)),

    # TRANSFORMING AN IMAGE RANDOMLY
    layers.experimental.preprocessing.RandomFlip("horizontal"),
    # layers.experimental.preprocessing.RandomFlip("vertical"),
    layers.experimental.preprocessing.RandomRotation(0.25),
    layers.experimental.preprocessing.RandomZoom(0.25),

    # Image Convolutional Layers
    layers.Conv2D(32, 3, padding="same", activation="relu"),
    layers.AveragePooling2D(2),
    layers.Dropout(0.35),
    layers.Conv2D(64, 3, padding="same", activation="relu"),
    layers.AveragePooling2D(2),
    layers.Dropout(0.35),
    layers.Conv2D(128, 3, padding="same", activation="relu"),
    layers.AveragePooling2D(2),
    layers.Dropout(0.2),


    # Flattening the Matrix to 1-D Array
    layers.Flatten(),

    # Deep Neural Network
    # layers.BatchNormalization(),
    # layers.Dense(128, activation="relu"),
    # layers.Dense(200, activation="relu"),
    # layers.Dropout(0.3),
    # layers.Dense(800, activation="relu"),
    # layers.Dropout(0.3),
    # layers.Dense(80, activation="relu"),
    # layers.BatchNormalization(),
    # layers.Dropout(0.6),
    # layers.Dense(800, activation="relu"),
    # layers.Dropout(0.6),
    # layers.Dense(400, activation="relu"),
    # layers.Dropout(0.6),
    # layers.Dense(20, activation="relu"),

    # Output layer with final value between 0 and 1
    layers.Dense(1, activation="sigmoid"),
])
# model.summary()

model.compile(
    optimizer = "adam",
    loss = "binary_crossentropy",
    metrics = ["accuracy"]
)
valAccCallback = tf.keras.callbacks.EarlyStopping(
	monitor = 'val_accuracy',
	patience = 80,
	min_delta = 0.01,
	mode = 'max',
)
with tf.device("/GPU:0"):
    history = model.fit(
        X_train,
        y_train,
        epochs = 10,
        batch_size = 32,
        validation_data = (X_test, y_test),
        callbacks = [valAccCallback]
    )

# PLOTTING THE GRAPH
history = history.history

fig, axes = plt.subplots(1, 2, figsize = (16, 4))
fig.subplots_adjust(wspace=0.5)

for i, metric in enumerate(['loss','accuracy']):
    axes[i].plot(history[metric], color='blue', label=f"train {metric}")
    axes[i].plot(history['val_'+metric], color='red', label=f"test {metric}")
    axes[i].set_title(f"Comparing {metric}")
    axes[i].set_xlabel("epochs")
    axes[i].set_ylabel(metric)
    axes[i].legend()

plt.plot()

# SAVING THE MODEL IF TEST ACCURACY IS INCREASED
import pickle

test_acc = model.evaluate(X_test, y_test)[1]
print("\nTest Accuracy:", test_acc)
test_acc = round(test_acc * 100, 1)
if test_acc >= 86:
    print(f"Saved the Model with an accuracy of: %.1f%%"%test_acc)
    # pickle.dump(model, open(f"model_%.1f.pkl"%test_acc, "wb"))
    model.save(f"model_%.1f.h5"%test_acc)
else:
    print(f"Did not save the Model, Accuracy was only %.1f%%"%test_acc)
